This allows it to automatically revise its work in many situations. Similarly this means **Agent** mode can typically handle more complex and multi-step tasks. That's just a brief intro and there is much more to learn, but that's for a dedicated future exercise. Remember, AI assistants often produce different results, even if the same prompt is provided. +	provider, err := githubProvider.New("test-token")

+	testCases := []struct {
+		name        string
+		issueNumber any
+		expected    int
+	}{

+			name:        "int",
+			issueNumber: 123,
+			expected:    123,
+		},
+		{
+			name:        "float64",
+			issueNumber: float64(456),
+			expected:    456,
+		},
+		{
+			name:        "string number",
+			issueNumber: "789",
+			expected:    789,
+		},
+	}
+
+	for _, testCase := range testCases {
+		t.Run(testCase.name, func(t *testing.T) {
+			// We can't test the actual API call without mocking, but we can test parameter validation
+			result := provider.ExecuteTool(context.Background(), types.ToolCall{
+				Name: "github_get_issue",
+				Arguments: map[string]any{
+					"owner":        "test-owner",
+					"repo":         "test-repo",
+					"issue_number": testCase.issueNumber,
+				},
+			})
+
+			// The call will fail because we're using a test token, but it should pass validation
+			// and fail at the API call level, not parameter validation
+			assert.False(t, result.Success) // Expected to fail due to invalid token
+			assert.NotEqual(t, "issue_number parameter must be a number", result.Error)
+			assert.NotEqual(t, "issue_number must be a positive integer", result.Error)
+		})
+	}

+func TestExecuteGetIssue_ContextCanceled_IsRetryable(t *testing.T) {
+	provider, err := githubProvider.New("test-token")
+	require.NoError(t, err)
+
+	ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())
+	cancel()
+
+	result := provider.ExecuteTool(ctx, types.ToolCall{
+		Name: "github_get_issue",
+		Arguments: map[string]any{
+			"owner":        "ondatra-ai",
+			"repo":         "flow-test-go",
+			"issue_number": 1,
+		},
+	})
+
+	assert.False(t, result.Success)
+	lw, ok := result.ContextWrites["last_error"].(map[string]any)
+	require.True(t, ok)
+	assert.Equal(t, "retryable", lw["class"])
+}
+
+func TestExecuteGetIssue_HTTPError_IsFatal(t *testing.T) {
+	provider, err := githubProvider.New("invalid-token")
+	require.NoError(t, err)
+
+	result := provider.ExecuteTool(context.Background(), types.ToolCall{
+		Name: "github_get_issue",
+		Arguments: map[string]any{
+			"owner":        "ondatra-ai",
+			"repo":         "flow-test-go",
+			"issue_number": 1,
+		},
+	})
+
+	assert.False(t, result.Success)
+	lw, ok := result.ContextWrites["last_error"].(map[string]any)
+	require.True(t, ok)
+	assert.Equal(t, "fatal", lw["class"])
+	_, hasStatus := lw["status"]
+	assert.True(t, hasStatus)
+}
